          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The morphological closing of an image is defined as a dilation followed by an erosion. Closing can remove small dark spots (i.e. \"pepper\") and connect small bright cracks. This tends to \"close\" up (dark) gaps between (bright) features."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
